# Evidence-Based Writing

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p8w1qe"
opinion
=
unsupported
belief
```

or:

```text id="u3w6qe"
evidence
=
extra
details
```

Some may:

```text id="c5w9qe"
repeat
claim
without
support
```

without understanding:

```text id="k2w4qe"
strong writing
needs
reasons
and
evidence
```

Students may also think:

```text id="n6w3qe"
louder language
=
better argument
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="t1w7qe"
quality evidence
strengthens
writing
```

Example:

student writes:

```text id="q7w2qe"
School uniforms
are best
because
I said so
```

instead of:

```text id="v4w8qe"
School uniforms
may reduce
clothing distraction
and support
school identity
```

because:

```text id="a5w3qe"
claims
need
support
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="g3w7rx"
reasoned opinion
```

For Grade 5:

focus includes:

Opinion Writing:

* claim
* reasons
* organization
* transitions
* conclusion

Evidence:

* facts
* examples
* experiences
* explanation
* support

Important idea:

```text id="v9w1rt"
opinions
become stronger
with
evidence
```

